<title>USA: Oracle sees $0.06/shr charge for deal.</title>
<headline>Oracle sees $0.06/shr charge for deal.</headline>
<dateline>REDWOOD SHORES, Calif. 1997-08-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Oracle Corp said Monday it would take a fiscal first-quarter charge of $90 million, or $0.06 a share post-split, for the acquisition of Treasury Services Corp.</p>
<p>The per-share figure takes into account a three-for-two stock split slated to take place later this month. Pre-split, the per-share figure would be $0.09, said David Roux, Oracle executive vice president.</p>
<p>Oracle said today it had agreed to buy closely held TSC for $120 million cash to beef up its line of banking software products.</p>
